Police found mandrax, crystal meth and cocaine rocks at a house in Sophiatown, Johannesburg. JOHANNESBURG - Two suspects have been arrested after they were caught with drugs worth over R100,000 in Sophiatown, Johannesburg. Police found mandrax, crystal meth and cocaine rocks at a house in the area. Police spokesperson captain Mavela Masondo said: “Drugs are one of the problems that we encounter in our province, and that’s why the provincial commissioner decided we need to go out in full force and arrest drug dealers.” The suspects will appear at the Sophiatown Magistrate's Court on Monday. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)